@@TJvDeleteError
<TITLEIMG TJvDeleteError>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.??
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Displays a dialog box for errors encountered when deleting a file
Description
  This component is used to display a dialog box encountered when deleting a file during a setup
  routine. It is a wrapper for the SetupDeleteError API call.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDeleteError.Execute
Summary
  Shows the dialog box
Description
  This method shows the SetupDeleteError dialog box
Return value
  This method returns dsSuccess if the user pressed "Retry", dsCancel if the user pressed
  "Cancel", dsSkipFile if the user pressed "Skip File", and dsError if an error occured.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDeleteError.FileName
Summary
  The filename listed in the dialog box
Description
  This property contains the complete pathname of the file that was being deleted when the error
  occured.
See Also
  Win32ErrorCode
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDeleteError.Style
Summary
  Flags used for modifying the dialog box
Description
  These flags modify how the dialog box is presented to the user.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDeleteError.Win32ErrorCode
Summary
  Error code listed in the dialog box
Description
  This property contains the Windows error code that occured for presentation to and
  interpretation for the user.
